## Why Tradespeople in South Wales Need a Website

If you're a tradesperson in South Wales — whether you're a plumber, electrician, builder or decorator — having a website is no longer a "nice-to-have." It's a necessity. At [NC Digital](/), we build fast, mobile-ready websites that help local trades stand out and get more work.

Most customers search online before picking up the phone. **And if they can't find you — they'll find someone else.** That's why we focus on clean builds, strong local SEO, and [WordPress websites](https://wordpress.org/) designed to help you grow.

> "Trades deserve websites that work as hard as they do — generating leads and showing off real work. That's what we build at NC Digital."
> NC Digital

#### Why Every Tradesperson Should Be Online

When someone searches for "plumber near me" or "builder in Merthyr," you want to show up — ideally before your competitors. [Google](https://www.google.com/) is often your first impression, and without a proper website, you're invisible to new customers.

Our builds focus on [local SEO](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/7451184?hl=en), making it easier for your business to be found in your area — from Merthyr to Cardiff.

#### What You Get with a Website from NC Digital

- 5-page [WordPress website](https://wordpress.org/showcase/) built for trades
- Mobile-ready and easy to use
- Local SEO structure to rank in your area
- UK-based secure hosting
- Full access — no lock-ins, no templates

#### Serving South Wales — Built in Merthyr Tydfil

NC Digital is based in Merthyr, and we work with trades and small businesses across South Wales — including [Ebbw Vale](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebbw_Vale), [Pontypridd](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pontypridd), [Caerphilly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caerphilly), and [Cardiff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiff). We know the local market and build websites that win work.

#### Let's Get You Set Up — and Seen

**If you're a tradesperson and still relying on just social media or word of mouth, now's the time to go further.** A website puts your work in front of more people — and turns visits into enquiries.

